<br>
I respect your position and your point of view, however it is only one of many.<br>
<br>
Scheduling via a calendar may suit your needs very well, but it does not work for everyone.  Furthermore, it has pitfalls and exploits of its own -- a race to a plane becomes a race to the calendar to schedule it, everyone wants to schedule on friday, saturday and sunday, etc..<br>
<br>
Just as you're a player with a lot of RL responsibilities, there are a lot of players with next to none.  Calendars do not suit their needs, and scheduling adds an uncomfortable sense of clockwork to the game -- adventurers in fantasy literature don't check their watches before killing a dragon after all.  <br>
<br>
In other words, a calendar may help you, but it inhibits others.<br>
<br>
So, you have the situation we have here.  Different types of people with different beliefs, philosophies, desires and needs playing the same game, coexisting in the same world.<br>
<br>
Telling a player or a guild that they have to conform to your views is as wrong as them telling you that you must adapt to theirs -- and that's exactly what most calendar zealots do.<br>
<br>
Who decides what is right?  The guys running the game, Verant.  They do not support calendars.  As far as they're concerned, the first party to a plane or a mobs has rights to it -- application of this general rule does vary GM to GM.<br>
<br>
I'm not against calendars.  I think they can be a useful *tool*.  However, they are not -- and should not be treated as -- the law. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/usotae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sotae</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 226<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/2/01 5:01:57 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.dencity.com/pactum/sotae.gif HEIGHT="304" WIDTH="141"></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sacret Fires, CC and the calender.</span><hr size=1> ok i guess i'll finally make a real reply to all of this...<br>
